\f0\b\fs38 \cf0 I didn\'92t get notifications for my flight?\

\fs28  
\fs38 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qj\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf2 In order to receive notifications you have to make sure that background fetch is enabled. Which is not the case if you are in Low Power Mode. Furthermore the app has to stay in the background, meaning you must not swipe it up from the multitasking switcher after exiting FlightStatus. Additionally you have to make sure that you allowed FlightStatus to send you notifications. You should get a notification 90 minutes before your flight, this is a good way of seeing if everything works. Other notifications will be periodically as new data becomes available. 
\fs32 \cf0 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

